Project Report on Travel Booking Platform Using Agile
1. Introduction

A Travel Booking Platform is an online system that allows users to search and book flights, trains, hotels, and travel packages. This project is designed to make booking easier and faster for customers. Agile methodology is used to build the project in small and manageable parts.

2. Objective

To allow users to search travel options

To provide easy booking and payment

To show booking history

To provide cancellation and refund options

3. Scope

Features included:

User registration and login

Search flights/hotels

Booking confirmation

Payment integration (demo)

Booking history and cancellation

4. Agile Approach

Agile helps to build the system sprint by sprint with continuous feedback.

Sprints

Sprint 1: User login + basic UI
Sprint 2: Search and filter system
Sprint 3: Booking + payment simulation
Sprint 4: Cancellation + final testing

5. Tools & Technologies

Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript

Backend: Java / Python / PHP

Database: MySQL

Tools: VS Code, GitHub

6. Advantages

Easy booking from anywhere

Saves time and effort

Better customer experience

Real-time availability

7. Conclusion

This travel booking platform is useful for users to plan trips easily. Agile methodology made the development smooth and flexible because changes could be done anytime in sprints.
